snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve watched every Liverpool game this season and that was by far the toughest game we’ve had, including in Europe, Wolves were superb. The job Santo is doing there is phenomenal. Little money, European commitments as well and they ran us ragged in the second half. Yeah we were in good positions to grab a second if Salah wasn’t so greedy but Wolves were excellent. Good luck for the rest of the season WWFC.

Just one thing though, what was the injury time all about? I know there were subs but they were all done very quickly yet there was still four minutes. Only two in the first half though, with Mane going down and the Wolves lad (can’t remember who) being down for a while. Why don’t they just stop the clock like rugby and do away with completely random injury time?
